<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, in Zend_Controller_Action, there is a convention implied by initView that the following directory structure exists:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
controllers/
    ...
views/
    scripts/
    helpers/
    filters/
</code></pre>

<p>The idea would be to provide a single method that assumes this convention if the other paths are not explicitly set already.  For example if $view-&gt;setBasePath('../application/user/views') is set, i can then assume scripts will be in ../application/user/views/scripts, helpers in ../application/user/views/helpers, and filters in ../application/user/views/filters.</p>

<p>This is a convenience method, low priority, but it makes sense to have as it encourages a good convention to follow, as well as suggests a way of doing things that other components (namely zend-controller) prefer.</p>

<p>-ralph</p>

